    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-12-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-12-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="6"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d6">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Buchanan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-12-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 21, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 428.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose for your information copy of a note
                    from the Argentine minister at this capital informing the Department that you
                    had been selected by the Argentine and Chilean Governments to act as third
                    arbitrator in the matter of the Puna de Atacama boundary line, in case the
                    delegates of the two countries who are to meet on March 10 next fail to reach an
                    agreement concerning it.</p>
                <p>Copy of the Department’s reply is also inclosed.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
